<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="646" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300 114 /01.3</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-23">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1914</hi>.</date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 1:30 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>887. United States Steel Products Company, 30 Church Street, New York,
                            urging through London manager that Embassy make representations to
                            British Government with a view to having raised embargo on shipments of
                            manganese ore from India to United States. Manager states company
                            dependent upon this source of <pb facs="0733" n="419" xml:id="pg_419"/>
                            supply and if embargo not raised will sustain great loss. Further that
                            two steamers loaded with company’s ore are held in Bombay whose speedy
                            release is desired. Please instruct.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>